  • Class
    Description
    FridgeCoupledModel
    The class FridgeCoupledModel defines a simple coupled model used to assemble the models defined for the Fridge in order to execute unit tests on the Fridge simulator.
    FridgeElectricityModel
    The class FridgeElectricityModel defines a simulation model for the electricity consumption of the Fridge.
    FridgeElectricityModel.FridgeElectricityReport
    The class FridgeElectricityReport implements the simulation report for the FridgeElectricityModel.
    FridgeElectricityModel.FridgeState
    The enumeration FridgeState describes the operation states of the Fridge.
    FridgeTemperatureModel
    The class FridgeTemperatureModel defines a simulation model for the temperature inside the fridge.
    FridgeTemperatureModel.FridgeTemperatureReport
    The class FridgeTemperatureReport implements the simulation report for the FridgeTemperatureModel.
    FridgeTemperatureModel.State
    The enumeration State defines the state in which the Fridge can be from the temperature perspective.
    FridgeUnitTesterModel
    The class FridgeUnitTesterModel defines a model that is used to test the models defining the Fridge simulator.
    InternalTemperatureModel
    The class InternalTemperatureModel defines a simulation model for the environment, namely the Internal temperature of the house.
    RunFridgeUnitarySimulation
    The class RunFridgeUnitarySimulation creates a simulator for the Fridge and then runs a typical simulation.
